PORT ELIZABETH, March 9 – Health Minister Zweli Mkhize has announced on Monday afternoon that four more people, all from KwaZulu-Natal (KZN) have tested positive for Covid-19, bringing the number of reported cases in South Africa to seven. The minister said on national television that another couple from Howick, had tested positive. He said a 45-year-old man from the Pietermaritzburg area and a 38-year-old-man from Pietermaritzburg had also tested prositive for the virus. All four people were part of a group of ten people who visited Italy recently. The minister said that all have been quarantined and that the department was awaiting test results for others from the group of ten. – African News Agency (ANA)